title: Stanford wide receiver hauls in catch of the year
text:
Sports are fun not just because we want our teams to win, but sometimes, sports do things that make us stop and say, "How?"
That happened Thursday night.
During Stanford's 56-35 win over UCLA, Cardinal wide receiver Francis Owusu made the catch of the season.
The play started with a razzle-dazzle reverse back to quarterback Kevin Hogan who then launched the ball to the end zone. His throw was short, but Owusu still made the grab.
How?
Without looking, he pinned the ball to the back of UCLA's Jaleel Wadood.
Again, HOW?
Relive Francis Owusu's INSANE catch -- our #12Best Moment from #UCLAvsSTAN on ESPN! #Pac12FB

How?
(I had to say it again).
